ARTISTIC youngsters from Glasgow got a front row seat when they paid a visit to the theatre. Stage set for pupils ARTISTIC youngsters from Glasgow got a front row seat when they paid a visit to the theatre.The children from St Ninian's Primary School in Great Western Road have been working with printmaker Ursula Hunter to create a decorative piece of art to be displayed in the Theatre Royal.The special artwork was created for the Arts &amp; Business Scotland Awards.Arts &amp; Business Scotland has been working for more than 25 years to create relationships between business and culture to enable Scotland to benefit from a vibrant cultural community.The awards celebrate and showcase the best examples of business partnerships and sponsorships with cultural organisations in Scotland. 